SIMPLE: pestiferous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pestiferous
<hw>Pes*tif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pestiferus</ets>, <ets>pestifer</ets>; <ets>pestis</ets> pest +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear: cf. F. <ets>pestif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Pest-bearing; pestilential; noxious to health;
malignant; infectious; contagious; <as>as, <ex>pestiferous</ex>
bodies</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Poor, <xex>pestiferous</xex> creatures begging
alms.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Evelyn.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Unwholesome and
<xex>pestiferous</xex> occupations.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Burke.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Noxious to peace, to morals, or to society; vicious;
hurtful; destructive; <as>as, a <ex>pestiferous</ex>
demagogue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pestiferous</qex> reports of men very nobly held.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pestiferously</ent>⟦br⟧
